{"questionId":"9067312","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">A student synthesized aspirin, acetylsalicylic acid, in a school laboratory.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><img style=\"margin-right:auto;margin-left:auto;display:block;\" src=\"__IMG__/af1a8f4d885f34fb3ff17759315f51472889ddf2.png\" width=\"203\" height=\"273\"></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">0.300 g of crude aspirin was dissolved in ethanol and titrated with sodium hydroxide solution, NaOH (aq).</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">NaOH (aq) + C<sub>9</sub>H<sub>8</sub>O<sub>4</sub> (in ethanol) → NaC<sub>9</sub>H<sub>7</sub>O<sub>4</sub> (aq) + H<sub>2</sub>O (l)</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Determine the percentage purity of the synthesized aspirin.</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">«&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{\\text{0}}{\\text{.293 g}}}}{{0.300{\\text{ g}}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>0</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>.293 g</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>0.300</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>&nbsp;g</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> ×&nbsp;100% » = 97.7 «%»&nbsp; <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9067312","referenceCode":"19M.3.sl.TZ2.b(ii)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Determine the percentage purity of the synthesized aspirin.","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b(ii)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Options","Options","D: Medicinal chemistry","D.2 Aspirin and penicillin","Options","D: Medicinal chemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}